======================================================================
THEOREM: EXACT Q_k LIMITS
======================================================================

For the Interval tournament C_p^{1..m} with m=(p-1)/2, as p→∞:

  k odd:  Q_k = p² cos²(kπ/(2p)) / (k²π²(p/(kπ))²·sin²(πk/p))
        = cos²(kπ/(2p)) / sin²(kπ/p)
        → 1/(2sin(kπ/(2p))·cos(kπ/(2p)))² × cos²(kπ/(2p))
  Wait, let me redo this properly.

  For ALL k (both parities):
    Q_k = sin²(mπk/p) / sin²(πk/p)
    Let α = πk/p. Then mα = (p-1)α/(2) = kπ/2 - kπ/(2p)
    sin(mα) = sin(kπ/2 - kπ/(2p))

    k odd:  = ±cos(kπ/(2p))
    k even: = ±sin(kπ/(2p))  [since sin(kπ/2)=0 for even k]

    sin(α) = sin(πk/p) = sin(kπ/(2p)·2) = 2sin(kπ/(2p))cos(kπ/(2p))

    k odd:  Q_k = cos²(kπ/(2p)) / (4sin²(kπ/(2p))cos²(kπ/(2p)))
                = 1 / (4sin²(kπ/(2p)))
                → 1 / (4·(kπ/(2p))²) = p²/(k²π²)

    k even: Q_k = sin²(kπ/(2p)) / (4sin²(kπ/(2p))cos²(kπ/(2p)))
                = 1 / (4cos²(kπ/(2p)))
                → 1/4

  BEAUTIFUL UNIFIED FORMULA:
    Q_k = 1/(4sin²(kπ/(2p)))  if k is odd
    Q_k = 1/(4cos²(kπ/(2p)))  if k is even

Verification of unified formula:

  p=97:
    k=1: actual=953.41435459, formula=953.41435459, match=True
    k=2: actual=0.25026242, formula=0.25026242, match=True
    k=3: actual=106.00904123, formula=106.00904123, match=True
    k=4: actual=0.25105189, formula=0.25105189, match=True
    k=5: actual=38.21668339, formula=38.21668339, match=True
    k=6: actual=0.25237508, formula=0.25237508, match=True
    k=7: actual=19.53928297, formula=19.53928297, match=True

  p=997:
    k=1: actual=100714.25176451, formula=100714.25176451, match=True
    k=2: actual=0.25000248, formula=0.25000248, match=True
    k=3: actual=11190.54649272, formula=11190.54649272, match=True
    k=4: actual=0.25000993, formula=0.25000993, match=True
    k=5: actual=4028.65007161, formula=4028.65007161, match=True
